<div id="help" style="display: none;">
<ul>
	<li>
	<u>What is a shiz period?</u>
	<br />
	<span style="color:green;">A shiz period begins at the beginning of each month and ends the last day of the month.<br />
	This means all previous periods are archived and you can no longer post or interact 
	with periods that have past, However you will still be able to read shiz from past periods. Please check the archive section. 
	<br />
	On each new period the slate is cleaned and ready for action, the gives a chance for new evolving content each period.</span>  
	</li>
	<li>
	<b>What do green categories, content and comments mean?</b><br />
	Shiz highlighted with green was created by you!!
	</li>
	<li>
	<b>Why are there no names or dates on anything?</b><br />
	This is to have some level of anonimity, lessen the bias on material. and lessen boundries. 
	</li>
	<li>
	<b>What can we not post?<b/>
	Please read the rules and please respect them
	</li>
	<li>
	
	</li>
	<li>
	<b>Why are some categories larger than others?</b>
	As content grows inside a category so does its popularity as well as the font size. This is to emphasize which categories are the top shiz!
	</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div id="what" style="display: none;">
<ul>
	<li>
	<b>What is this?</b>
	<br />
	This is another BBS sytle web board! It is pseudo-anonymous (hard to be truly anonymous), yes you have to register, but you only need to enter the username you want and password. None of your information
	will be posted on the web board, there is no usernames or other information rendered on categories, content, or comments. 
	</li>
	<li>
	<b>If anoymous, why have a registration?</b><br />
	This is to make your experience better, it avoids having to enter tap codes etc. Also if you are a high quality contributor, we would like to make your experience even better. 
	</li>
</ul>
